hopobject.body: I'm interested in this position crowdmed.com reviews From the ARM based CPU and Qualcomm Adreno 330 GPU we can surmise it'll be sporting a Snapdragon 800 processor at its heart. And based on previous rumours of a 10.1-inch screen that 1371 x 771 resolution will deliver a meagre 156ppi. Even at 7-inches that screen would only offer 225ppi. Here's hoping that's not the final screen or Nokia may be in trouble from the start of its tablet outing.
